{{Quote|The stillness of Empty Meditation allows Jedi to center themselves and achieve deep inner peace.|[[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Skarch Vaunk]]|<ref name="The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref>}}

The '''Meditation of Emptiness''', also known as '''Empty Meditation''' or '''Emptiness''', was a technique used by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] to purge oneself of feelings to create an emotional anchor. A [[Force power/Legends#Control|Control]]-based [[Force power/Legends|Force power]], where an individual emptied their mind and allowed [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to flow through them, entering a deep [[Meditation/Legends|meditation]]. The individual was oblivious to their surroundings, and they hungered and dehydrated as normal. Individuals in states of Emptiness were difficult to detect in the Force, and Force powers of sensing or seeking directed at them had little or no effect. Entering a Meditation of Emptiness cleared and strengthened the individual's connection to the Force, allowing them greater control for a limited period of time after exiting Emptiness.
==Overview==
[[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] were taught this [[Meditation/Legends|meditative]] ability, which involved emptying themselves of feelings and opening themselves to [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. This shedding of emotions and feelings allowed the user to center themselves in simple power as well as the strength of the Force. [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] explained that this act was like finding an eye of calm within the center of one's storm of emotions.

Through this act, all memories as well as thoughts and feelings were ignored or treated as if they were shadows which allowed a Jedi to find a place where there was nothing else but peace.

Meditation of Emptiness was also an effective technique for a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to use to combat external mental influence or attack, such as the [[Mind trick/Legends|Jedi mind trick]].<ref name="Scourge (novel)">[[Scourge (novel)|''Scourge'']]</ref>

